Keeping clothes fresh in Srinagar means more than a quick wash — suits, silk sarees, pherans, wool shawls, and delicate fabrics need proper dry cleaning or specialist laundry care. Panun Kaergar connects you with dry clean and laundry services across Srinagar, with convenient pickup and delivery to neighbourhoods like Hyderpora, Rajbagh, Bemina, and Hazratbal.

## What can you send for dry cleaning or laundry?

- **Formal wear** — suits, blazers, office shirts, trousers
- **Traditional and festive clothing** — sarees, lehengas, sherwanis, embroidered pieces
- **Winter garments** — wool coats, pherans, Kashmiri shawls, heavy jackets
- **Household linen** — curtains, bed covers, tablecloths, cushion covers
- **Everyday laundry** — regular clothes with wash, dry, and fold service

Always check garment labels and mention stains or special fabrics when booking so the provider uses the right treatment.

## Dry clean vs regular laundry

**Dry cleaning** uses solvents instead of water — ideal for structured garments, silk, wool, and items labelled "dry clean only." **Regular laundry** suits cotton, synthetics, and everyday wear that can be machine or hand washed.

For mixed wardrobes, you can book both services in one pickup. Separate items clearly and note any stain locations (collar, cuffs, hem) in your booking details.

## Pickup and delivery in Srinagar

Book a pickup time that works for you — morning or afternoon slots across most Srinagar areas. Providers collect from your door, process items at their facility, and return them pressed, folded, or on hangers as requested.

Typical turnaround is one to three days depending on volume and garment type. Rush service may be available — ask when booking.

## Care tips before sending clothes

- Empty pockets and remove belts or detachable accessories
- Point out stains — wine, oil, ink — so they can be pre-treated
- Note delicate embellishments — zari, beads, embroidery
- For shawls and wool, mention if you need moth-safe storage bags on return

## Storing cleaned garments in Srinagar

After winter, store wool and pherans in breathable bags with cedar blocks or moth repellent. Hang suits on wide-shoulder hangers to preserve shape. Keep silk sarees away from direct sunlight when storing — a well-pressed garment lasts longer with proper cupboard care.

